.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DATASOURCE 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.8.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-datasource \- datasource catalog, export, import, diff, browse, and mutation workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util datasource [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B grafana-util ds [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
grafana\-util datasource is the namespace for catalog lookup, live browsing, export/import, diff, and live create/modify/delete workflows. The same namespace is also available as grafana\-util ds.
.PP
Use this namespace when you want to inspect supported datasource types, browse live inventory, export a datasource bundle, compare a local bundle with Grafana, or create and maintain live datasources.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B types
Show the built\-in supported datasource type catalog. Use when: You need to see the canonical datasource type ids that the CLI normalizes and supports for create flows.
.TP
.B list
List live Grafana datasource inventory. Use when: You need a non\-interactive inventory of datasources, either for the current org, one explicit org, or across all visible orgs.
.TP
.B browse
Open a live datasource browser against Grafana with in\-place modify and delete actions. Use when: You want an interactive inventory view for inspecting, editing, or deleting live datasources.
.TP
.B inspect\-export
Inspect a local masked recovery bundle without connecting to Grafana. Use when: You want to read datasource export artifacts from disk and review them with text, table, CSV, JSON, YAML, or interactive output.
.TP
.B export
Export live Grafana datasource inventory as normalized JSON plus provisioning files. Use when: You need a local datasource bundle for later inspection, diff, or import.
.TP
.B import
Import datasource inventory through the Grafana API. Use when: You have a local datasource bundle or provisioning tree and want to push it into Grafana, either live or as a dry run.
.TP
.B diff
Compare datasource inventory from a local bundle against live Grafana and print an operator\-summary diff report. Use when: You want a concise live\-versus\-local difference report before import.
.TP
.B add
Create one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API. Use when: You want to create a new datasource directly, or dry\-run the create step before applying it.
.TP
.B modify
Modify one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API. Use when: A datasource already exists and you need to update its URL, auth, JSON payload, or other live settings.
.TP
.B delete
Delete one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API. Use when: A datasource should be removed by UID or by name, either as a dry run or as an acknowledged live delete.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-url
Grafana base URL.
.TP
.B \-\-token, \-\-basic\-user, \-\-basic\-password
shared live Grafana credentials.
.TP
.B \-\-profile
load repo\-local defaults from grafana\-util.yaml.
.TP
.B \-\-color
control JSON color output for the namespace.
.SH WORKFLOW NOTES
.PP
Datasource export follows a masked recovery contract. Treat the canonical export JSON as the replay source. Treat provisioning output as a derived projection for Grafana provisioning workflows.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
grafana\-util datasource is the namespace for catalog lookup, live browsing, export/import, diff, and live create/modify/delete workflows. The same namespace is also available as grafana\-util ds.
.EX
grafana-util datasource --help
.EE
.PP
types: Show the built\-in supported datasource type catalog.
.EX
grafana-util datasource types
.EE
.PP
list: List live Grafana datasource inventory.
.EX
grafana-util datasource list --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --output-format text
.EE
.PP
browse: Open a live datasource browser against Grafana with in\-place modify and delete actions.
.EX
grafana-util datasource browse --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin
.EE
.PP
inspect\-export: Inspect a local masked recovery bundle without connecting to Grafana.
.EX
grafana-util datasource inspect-export --input-dir ./datasources --table
.EE
.PP
export: Export live Grafana datasource inventory as normalized JSON plus provisioning files.
.EX
grafana-util datasource export --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --export-dir ./datasources --overwrite
.EE
